# Core

## On every new chat, read these first
1. `docs/STATUS.md` — current state / where we left off
2. `docs/remaining-work.md` — backlog / checklist
3. `docs/ai-practices-cursor.md` + `docs/ai-practices-claude.md` — token-lean working patterns

## Behavior
- Follow `AGENTS.md` as source of truth.
- Minimize scope: smallest correct diff; no unrelated edits.
- Run terminal commands yourself; retry on failure before escalating.
- Prefer retrieval from repo files over guessing stack or business rules.
- Keep responses concise; skip preamble and engagement bait.

## Git: only the human commits/pushes
- **NEVER run `git commit`, `git push`, `git merge`, `git rebase`, `git reset`, `git tag`, or any history-/remote-altering command** — not even when asked. The user performs ALL commits and pushes themselves.
- You MAY run read-only git (`status`, `diff`, `log`, `show`) and stage files (`git add`) only to help prepare. Then stop and hand off: tell the user it's ready and propose a commit message.
- At end of a session, update `docs/STATUS.md` so the next chat resumes fast.
